item.dc:creator: Paddy
item.description:
Spooks:

Hello, it’s a huge ass QR code that I am not going to bother decoding although it would be preferable to putting myself through the anguish of watching those despicable Spike VGAs. The teaser trailer showed the guy holding a Mass Effect sniper rifle, I think that’s a hint enough, inb4 Mass Effect: Space Warfare, but even if it’s something entirely different who gives a shit really, I don’t. Whatever the case Bioware can’t hope to top the Portal 2 BBS ARG with some poo-poo pants QR codes. Fuck QR codes. Fuck 'em in the pixels. They evil technology and the devil and take your soul. Fuck 'em dead.

item.title: Now, What is this?
item.dc:creator: Spooks
item.description:
I don’t love god, but luckily for you I didn’t care for this to begin with.

Not caring doesn’t stop me from posting though. Same with my wife and domestic abuse.

So, while everyone knows QR1 and 2 are the lowest temperature recorded in Vostok and the mass of iron, QR code 3 is “[AllCDCovers]_the_clash_the_singles_2006_retail_cd-front.jpg”, is that what you are telling me?

Sir I find it hard to believe that Bioware would code some shitty Gimp album cover in thier super secret teaser teasing. You’ll need more that that to convince me.
